cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.NE, cs.DS 

The paper discusses the Support Vector Data Description (SVDD) approach for single-class classification and outlier detection, which is a common topic in machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.LG, cs.AI). The use of Gaussian kernel and the selection of kernel bandwidth parameter are also discussed, which are relevant to computer vision (cs.CV) and neural networks (cs.NE). The paper also proposes an extension of the Peak method for large datasets, which involves computational and algorithmic aspects of data science (cs.DS).
